    "Signal": {
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "description": "A measurable/sourceable parameter \u2014 the primary signal dimension.\n\nUsed for what's being measured or sourced: range defines the operating\nenvelope, accuracy/resolution define the quality of measurement.\nTop-level accuracy/resolution are defaults; ``specs`` holds condition-dependent\noverrides (e.g., accuracy varies with frequency).\n\nExample YAML (instrument):\n    signals:\n      voltage:\n        range: {min: 0.1, max: 1000, units: V}\n        accuracy: {pct_reading: 0.0035, pct_range: 0.0006}\n        resolution: {digits: 6.5}\n        specs:\n          - when:\n              frequency: {min: 3, max: 5, units: Hz}\n            accuracy: {pct_reading: 0.35, pct_range: 0.03}\n\nExample YAML (product):\n    signals:\n      voltage:\n        value: 3.3\n        units: V",
      "properties": {
        "range": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/$defs/RangeSpec"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null
        },
        "accuracy": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/$defs/AccuracySpec"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null
        },
        "resolution": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/$defs/ResolutionSpec"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null
        },
        "value": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "number"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Value"
        },
        "units": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Units"
        },
        "specs": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "items": {
                "$ref": "#/$defs/SpecBand"
              },
              "type": "array"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Specs"
        },
        "qualifier": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/$defs/SpecQualifier"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null
        },
        "note": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Note"
        }
      },
      "title": "Signal",
      "type": "object"
    },
    "SignalGroup": {
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "description": "Grouped signals forming a bus interface (ATML: Bus).\n\nUsed for protocols like I2C, SPI, UART where multiple signals\nmust be treated as a unit for routing and testing.\n\nExample YAML:\n    signal_groups:\n      i2c_main:\n        protocol: i2c\n        signals:\n          - pin: SDA\n            role: data\n          - pin: SCL\n            role: clock\n        parameters:\n          frequency: 400000",
      "properties": {
        "protocol": {
          "title": "Protocol",
          "type": "string"
        },
        "signals": {
          "items": {
            "$ref": "#/$defs/BusSignal"
          },
          "title": "Signals",
          "type": "array"
        },
        "parameters": {
          "additionalProperties": true,
          "title": "Parameters",
          "type": "object"
        },
        "description": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Description"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "protocol"
      ],
      "title": "SignalGroup",
      "type": "object"
    },
    "SpecBand": {
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "description": "Condition-dependent specification override for a parameter.\n\nEach band says \"at this operating point, here are the specs.\"\nThe ``when`` keys reference sibling parameter names (signals,\nconditions, or controls); multiple keys are ANDed (all must match).\nEmpty dict means unconditional (always applies).\n\nAny field that is ``None`` means \"no override \u2014 use the top-level default.\"\n\nExample YAML (accuracy varies with frequency):\n    specs:\n      - when:\n          frequency: {min: 3, max: 5, units: Hz}\n        accuracy: {pct_reading: 0.35, pct_range: 0.03}\n\nExample YAML (range derated at high frequency):\n    specs:\n      - when:\n          frequency: {min: 3e9, max: 6e9, units: Hz}\n        range: {min: -130, max: 5, units: dBm}\n        accuracy: {absolute: 0.8}",
      "properties": {
        "when": {
          "additionalProperties": {
            "anyOf": [
              {
                "$ref": "#/$defs/RangeSpec"
              },
              {
                "$ref": "#/$defs/PointSpec"
              },
              {
                "$ref": "#/$defs/ListSpec"
              },
              {
                "type": "string"
              },
              {
                "type": "number"
              },
              {
                "type": "boolean"
              },
              {
                "items": {
                  "anyOf": [
                    {
                      "type": "string"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "number"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "boolean"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                "type": "array"
              }
            ]
          },
          "title": "When",
          "type": "object"
        },
        "range": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/$defs/RangeSpec"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null
        },
        "value": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "number"
            },
            {
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Value"
        },
        "units": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Units"
        },
        "accuracy": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/$defs/AccuracySpec"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null
        },
        "resolution": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/$defs/ResolutionSpec"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null
        },
        "qualifier": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/$defs/SpecQualifier"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null
        },
        "note": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Note"
        }
      },
      "title": "SpecBand",
      "type": "object"
    },
    "SpecQualifier": {
      "description": "Qualification level for a specification value.\n\nMirrors industry convention from test equipment manufacturers:\n- **guaranteed**: Warranted spec \u2014 product must meet it, guardbanded for\n  measurement uncertainty and environmental variation.\n- **typical**: Expected performance measured across multiple units, not warranted.\n- **nominal**: Design target or expected value, not warranted or tested.\n- **supplemental**: Informational performance data, not warranted.",
      "enum": [
        "guaranteed",
        "typical",
        "nominal",
        "supplemental"
      ],
      "title": "SpecQualifier",
      "type": "string"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "description": "Product definition (ATML: UUT Description).\n\nTop-level model that ties together:\n- Product identification (id, name, revision)\n- Documentation references (datasheet, schematic)\n- Characteristics with condition matrices\n\nExample YAML:\n    product:\n      id: power_board_v1\n      name: \"DC-DC Power Board Rev A\"\n      revision: \"A\"\n      datasheet: \"docs/DS-001.pdf\"\n\n    characteristics:\n      rail_3v3_output:\n        function: dc_voltage\n        direction: output\n        units: V\n        pin: VOUT\n        specs:\n          - value: 3.3\n            accuracy: {pct_reading: 3.0}",
  "properties": {
